            <h2>Who Can Donate Plasma?</h2>
            <p>To donate plasma you will need to:</p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                <li>Be able to travel to a plasma donor centre in Birmingham, Reading, or Twickenham</li>
                <li>Be able to spare just over an hour to donate</li>
                <li>Be generally fit and well</li>
                <li>Be between the ages of 17 and 65 to start donating plasma. If you are over 65, you can start donating plasma if you have donated blood or platelets before (this must be within the last 2 years if you are over 69)</li>
                <li>Be over 50kg (7 stone 12 lbs) and have enough blood to donate safely. Check how much blood you have</li>
                <li>Have suitable veins and a normal pulse (we will check these before you donate)</li>
                <li>Meet all donor eligibility criteria (we'll discuss this with you before you donate)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

